# Steps to reproduce the problem
1. To reproduce the problem please use the MDN docs https://developer.mozilla.org
2. test the case by pasting below on MDN docs https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Date/toLocaleString
```js
const event = new Date(Date.UTC(2012, 11, 20, 3, 0, 0));
console.log(event.toLocaleString(['ky', 'kg', 'ky-KG', 'kyr'], { month: 'long' }));
//provided possible kyrgyz language tags but as it is not found the match tag it falls back to default language
``` 
3. verify the available options MDN docs https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/DateTimeFormat/supportedLocalesOf
```js
const locales1 = ['ky', 'ky-KG', 'kg'];
const options1 = { localeMatcher: 'lookup' };

console.log(Intl.DateTimeFormat.supportedLocalesOf(locales1, options1));
//no match found empty array
```

4. please verify the existance of language on different browser like Safari, FireFox and follow step 2, 3, it has to has a language support
```js
const locales1 = ['ky', 'ky-KG', 'kg'];
const options1 = { localeMatcher: 'lookup' };

console.log(Intl.DateTimeFormat.supportedLocalesOf(locales1, options1));
//language tag match found = Array ["ky", "ky-KG"]
```

# Problem Description
my application is using the Date.prototype.toLocaleString() method to get the Date with specified locale of date names. on Safari , FireFox its working but in Chromium is not working when i provide first parametr "ky-KG"

# Summary
Kyrgyz Language is not supported on chromium upon using Date.prototype.toLocaleString()

# Custom Questions
#### Which component does this fall under?
Blink>Javascript

#### Does this work in other browsers? 
Yes - This is just a Chrome problem

